Troube with the Hubble #哈勃望远镜的困境

The Hubble telescope was launched into space by NASA on April 20,
1990 at a cost of over a billion dollars. Right from the start 
there was trouble with the Hubble. The pictures it sent us were 
very disappointing because its main mirror was faulty! NASA is now 
going to put the telescope right, so it will soon be sending up 
four astronauts to repair it. The shuttle Endeavour will be taking
the astronauts to the Hubble. A robot-arm from the Endeavour will 
grab the telescope and hold it while the necessary repairs. Of 
course, the Hubble is above the earth's atmosphere, so it will 
soon be sending us the clearest pictures of the stars and distant 
galaxies that we have ever seen. The Hubble will tell us a great 
deal about the age and size of the universe. By the time you read 
this, the Hubble's eagle eye will have sent us thousands and 
thousands of wonderful pictures.

